And gladly wander up and down , And smile at toil and pain.gob I suffer on my three - score years , Till my Deliverer come , And wipe away his servant's tears , And take his exile home .
3 O what hath Jesus bought for me !
Rivers of life divine I see ,
3 O what hath Jesus bought for me ! Before my ravished eyes Rivers of life divine I see , And trees of paradise !
I see a world of spirits bright ,
They all are robed in spotless white ,
I see a world of spirits bright , Who taste the pleasures there ; They all are robed in spotless white , And conq'ring palms they bear ! fron Ston
4 O what are all my sufferings here ,
If , Lord , thou count me meet v
With that enraptured host t ' appear ,
Give joy or grief , give ease or pain ,
But let me find them all again

4 O what are all my sufferings here , If , Lord , thou count me meet v With that enraptured host t ' appear , And worship at thy feet ! Give joy or grief , give ease or pain , Take life or friends away ; But let me find them all again In that eternal day .
BLESS'D Jesus , what delicious fare- How sweet thine entertainments are !
